Description: Add Lokker app (https://github.com/tim-ecoder/Lokker.git) as privileged system app.
Version: v1.2a

Files:
  device/blackberry/athena/prebuilt/Lokker.apk  — prebuilt APK from GitHub releases
  device/blackberry/athena/prebuilt/Android.bp   — prebuilt module definition
  device/blackberry/athena/prebuilt/com.lokker.app.privapp-permissions.xml — privileged permissions
  device/blackberry/athena/device.mk             — added Lokker to PRODUCT_PACKAGES

Install location: system_ext/priv-app/Lokker/Lokker.apk
Signed with: platform certificate (signing-keys-old-sha384/platform.pk8)
APK source: https://github.com/tim-ecoder/Lokker/releases/tag/Lokker-v1.2a
Privileged permissions: MANAGE_USERS, CHANGE_COMPONENT_ENABLED_STATE, REMOVE_TASKS,
  REAL_GET_TASKS, WRITE_SECURE_SETTINGS, MANAGE_ACTIVITY_STACKS

Preprocessing (required — privileged apps must have uncompressed dex, Soong rejects
compressed dex). The upstream v1.2a release ships a Gradle-built APK with compressed
dex, so a local preprocess step is required before dropping into prebuilt/:

  1. Rebuild the APK with classes*.dex entries as ZIP_STORED (Python zipfile).
  2. zipalign -p -f 4
  3. apksigner sign --key platform.pk8 --cert platform.x509.pem --v2-signing-enabled true
     (signing-keys-old-sha384/platform.* — SHA-256 93940c5a5366d4d9...
      matches the upstream Lokker v2 signer, so the re-signed APK preserves
      cert identity and allows in-place upgrades.)

Upstream fix: add `androidResources { noCompress += ['dex'] }` to Lokker's
app/build.gradle to ship a preprocessed APK directly and skip these steps.
